{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889284431,"sessionID":"ses_284c05ab3ffeBmCKvtfLPbCBtr","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3fe1f4001tOvsLf6L3476n4","messageID":"msg_d7b3fdb3d001iqMH9VPvwfkShc","sessionID":"ses_284c05ab3ffeBmCKvtfLPbCBtr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c1223793687e4c08b5c6d55e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `FileType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n18:   - Types: `FileTypeRegular`, `FileTypeDirectory`, `FileTypeSymlink`, `FileTypeOther`\n19:   - String representation for each type\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `FileInfo` struct in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n22:   - Fields: `Name` (string), `Path` (string), `Size` (int64), `Mode` (os.FileMode), `ModTime` (time.Time), `IsDir` (bool), `FileType` (FileType)\n23:   - Constructor: `NewFileInfo(path string, info os.FileInfo) (*FileInfo, error)`\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `FileQuota` struct in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n26:   - Fields: `MaxFileSize` (int64), `MaxTotalSize` (int64), `MaxFiles` (int64), `MaxDirectoryDepth` (int)\n27:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n28:   - Validation rules: MaxFileSize > 0, MaxTotalSize > 0, MaxFiles > 0, MaxDirectoryDepth > 0\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `DefaultFileQuota()` function in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n31:   - Returns: MaxFileSize=10MB, MaxTotalSize=100MB, MaxFiles=1000, MaxDirectoryDepth=10\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define `QuotaUsage` struct in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n34:   - Fields: `UsedBytes` (int64), `MaxBytes` (int64), `FileCount` (int64), `MaxFiles` (int64), `PercentUsed` (float64)\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define `FileErrorType` and error constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n37:   - Types: `FileErrorNotFound`, `FileErrorPermission`, `FileErrorQuotaExceeded`, `FileErrorPathTraversal`, `FileErrorWrite`, `FileErrorRead`, `FileErrorSymlink`, `FileErrorDepth`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `FileError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n40:   - Fields: `Type` (FileErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n41:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n42: \n43: ### Phase 2: Path Validation Utilities\n44: \n45: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ValidatePath()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n46:   - Validates path is within workspace boundary\n47:   - Returns absolute path or error\n48:   - Prevents path traversal attacks\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `ResolvePath()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n51:   - Resolves path to absolute, following symlinks\n52:   - Returns error if symlink target is outside workspace\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `GetDepth()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n55:   - Calculates directory depth of a path\n56:   - Returns depth as integer\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `IsWithinWorkspace()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n59:   - Checks if resolved path is within workspace\n60:   - Uses filepath.Abs and strings.HasPrefix\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `ValidateDepth()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n63:   - Validates path depth does not exceed maximum\n64:   - Returns error if depth exceeds limit\n65: \n66: ### Phase 3: FileSystem Interface Definition\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `FileSystem` interface in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n69:   - Methods:\n70:     - `Read(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)`\n71:     - `ReadStream(ctx context.Context, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)`\n72:     - `Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error`\n73:     - `WriteStream(ctx context.Context, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error`\n74:     - `Delete(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n75:     - `DeleteAll(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n76:     - `Exists(ctx context.Context, path string) (bool, error)`\n77:     - `Info(ctx context.Context, path string) (*FileInfo, error)`\n78:     - `List(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)`\n79:     - `Mkdir(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error`\n80:     - `MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error`\n81:     - `Rename(ctx context.Context, oldPath, newPath string) error`\n82:     - `Copy(ctx context.Context, srcPath, dstPath string) error`\n83:     - `Quota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)`\n84: \n85: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `fileSystem` struct in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n86:   - Fields: `workDir` (string), `quota` (*FileQuota), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n87:   - Implements FileSystem interface\n88: \n89: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `NewFileSystem()` constructor in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n90:   - Creates fileSystem instance with workDir, quota, logger\n91: \n92: ### Phase 4: File Read Operations\n93: \n94: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `Read()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n95:   - Flow: ValidatePath → Check exists → Read file → Return []byte\n96:   - Handle FileErrorNotFound, FileErrorPathTraversal, FileErrorRead\n97: \n98: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `ReadStream()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n99:   - Opens file with streaming support\n100:   - Returns io.ReadCloser\n101:   - Validates path before opening\n102: \n103: ### Phase 5: File Write Operations\n104: \n105: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `Write()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n106:   - Flow: ValidatePath → Check quota → Write temp file → Atomic rename\